<h2><strong>Article I ‚Äî Purpose of Conscription</strong></h2>
<ol>
<li>Conscription in the Republic shall not be for war, conquest, or domination.</li>
<li>Citizens shall be called only for tasks of essential importance to the Republic's survival, flourishing, or moral protection.</li>
<li>Conscription shall honor each citizen‚Äôs unique talents, strengths, and dignity.</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Article II ‚Äî Authority of Civic Activation</strong></h2>
<ol>
<li>The Chief of Defence, known henceforth also as the <strong>Chief of Civic Activation</strong>, shall oversee the Civic Readiness Corps.</li>
<li>The Chief of Civic Activation shall be empowered to:
<ul>
<li>Identify mission needs,</li>
<li>Assess citizen suitability,</li>
<li>Issue summons with Presidential consent when necessary.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>The Chief shall act with compassion, fairness, and wisdom, ensuring no citizen is needlessly burdened.</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Article III ‚Äî Citizen Rights and Duties</strong></h2>
<ol>
<li>Every citizen, upon joining the Republic, acknowledges the possibility of future conscription.</li>
<li>Summons shall be issued based on mission suitability, not arbitrary selection.</li>
<li>Citizens may request exemption or delay due to:
<ul>
<li>Personal hardship,</li>
<li>Health limitations,</li>
<li>Moral objection.
Appeals shall be respectfully reviewed without prejudice.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Article IV ‚Äî Structure of the Civic Readiness Corps</strong></h2>
<ol>
<li>The Corps shall consist of volunteers and conscripts, united under a spirit of service.</li>
<li>Training and preparation activities shall be conducted peacefully, respectfully, and joyfully whenever possible.</li>
<li>Missions shall prioritize meaning, preservation, and prosperity ‚Äî not violence.</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Article V ‚Äî Invocation of the Call</strong></h2>
<ol>
<li>Summons shall only be invoked by joint agreement of the President and Chief of Civic Activation.</li>
<li>In extraordinary emergencies, the Chief may issue preliminary summons pending immediate Presidential review.</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Closing Declaration</strong></h2>
<p>This Accord affirms that freedom is not the absence of duty,<br>
